summary:
HSE Responsibilities:

- Carry out risk assessments for work at height activities and make sure that all work is Planned, Organised and carried out by a competent person ;
- Follow the  General Principles of Prevention for managing risks from work at height – take steps to avoid, prevent or reduce risks ;
- Chose the right work equipment and select collective measures to prevent falls (such as guard rails and working platforms) before other measures which may only reduce the distance and consequences of a fall (such as nets or airbags) or may only provide fall-arrest through personal protection equipment ;
- Preparing environmental documents and work procedures , occupational health and safety, emergencies and as to the duty;
- Regular and daily training staff on location; 
- Preparation of waste management and transport documents generated hazardous waste; 
- Preparing work permits for special operations; 
- Preparation of incident reports; 
- Drawing sheets nonconformities; 
- Implementation of HSE procedures of the company; 
- Participation in Audit-house, training related to the implementation of HSE procedures;

profile_positions.description:
The origins of Sirti lie in telecommunications, but it has now expanded beyond this sector. Sirti is high-speed, renewable energy, and the integration of systems, infrastructures and safety. Sirti is especially able to manage complex projects, involving thousands of people, with teams who work with dedication and professionalism, and constitute the real strength of this large Italian company that manages to combine a long history with an innovative spirit. 
Coordination of safety officers in Romania surveying H&S issues in activities performed by Sirti SpA employees for Enel , plus contractors employees: 
- Risk assessment; 
- Emergency situations management; 
- Accidents reporting and investigation; 
- Incidents and near misses reporting and investigation; 
- Field inspection; 
- H&S procedures development, updating and implementation; 
- Safety induction and training; 
- Contractors management, Work methods development and implementation; 
- Technical instructions revision and development; 
- Weekly, monthly and quarterly reporting; PPE endowment and acquisition;

- Develop and execute health and safety plans in the workplace according to legal guideline ;
- Prepare and enforce policies to establish a culture of health and safety ;
- Evaluate practices, procedures and facilities to assess risk and adherence to the law ;
- Conduct training and presentations for health and safety matters and accident prevention ;
- Monitor compliance to policies and laws by inspecting employees and operations ;
- Inspect equipment and machinery to observe possible unsafe conditions ;
- Investigate accidents or incidents to discover causes ;
- Recommend solutions to issues, improvement opportunities or new prevention measures ;
- Report on health and safety awareness, issues and statistics ;
